  "prompt": "How do you round to one decimal place?",
  "response": "To round a number to one decimal place, follow these steps:\n\n1. Look at the second decimal digit (the digit immediately to the right of the first decimal place).\n\n2. If this digit is 5 or greater, round up by increasing the first decimal digit by 1.\n\n3. If this digit is less than 5, keep the first decimal digit the same.\n\nExamples:\n- 3.46 rounds to 3.5\n- 2.73 rounds to 2.7\n- 4.15 rounds to 4.2\n- 6.04 rounds to 6.0\n\nSo in general: \n- 3.46 \u2192 3.5\n- 2.73 \u2192 2.7\n- 4.15 \u2192 4.2\n- 6.04 \u2192 6.0",
